
Ranger Help for: river
======================

SUMMARY:    
The river may not be smaller than a lake since its volume of water is
spread out over a long run. Its is usually charaterized by rushing 
fresh water down a gully or other lower land feature. Just as with 
lakes, Rangers don't live in rivers, but around them. They are great
source of food and can be found on most of the continents.

=============================================================================
SEE ALSO: Individual terrains

